Cheers!

267
00:16:41,520 --> 00:16:44,210
All right, allow me to introduce myself again.

268
00:16:44,990 --> 00:16:48,110
Fifth-grade student. Photography Department.
Kiryu Takashi.

269
00:16:48,470 --> 00:16:50,830
Thank you for the stop-motion animation
last time.

270
00:16:50,980 --> 00:16:55,060
No biggies! Thanks to all of you,
this club lives to see another year.

271
00:16:55,860 --> 00:16:59,460
Not to mention we have some cute girls among us.

272
00:17:01,530 --> 00:17:03,940
I'm Hiyama Yurika. Third-grade student
in the Handicraft Department.

273
00:17:04,240 --> 00:17:06,960
My main focus is pottery. Normally,
I make those things.

274
00:17:07,700 --> 00:17:19,150
Wheels on the bus go round and round.
Round and round.

275
00:17:22,109 --> 00:17:26,839
I'm Sugimoto Mikio, second-grade
Music Department student. Nice to meet you.

276
00:17:27,160 --> 00:17:29,650
Don't be fooled by his appearance.
He sings really well.

277
00:17:29,920 --> 00:17:31,550
All eyes on me!

278
00:17:32,250 --> 00:17:34,720
Let me celebrate this joy with a dance.

279
00:17:35,110 --> 00:17:36,770
This is the welcoming posture.

280
00:17:37,070 --> 00:17:38,940
This shows the excitement we have
towards the future.

281
00:17:39,400 --> 00:17:45,250
-He's Kakihara Sho, a third-grade dancer.
-This is the expression of love.

282
00:17:46,610 --> 00:17:49,730
And this is the Dance of Bacchus!

283
00:17:49,910 --> 00:17:51,410
Finally!

284
00:17:51,890 --> 00:17:53,850
The treasure of this club will
make its appearance soon.

285
00:17:54,130 --> 00:17:56,850
Mount Vesuvius Eruption!

286
